https://gian.org/multilingual_data/vehicle-disinfectant-bay-by-bisu-hang-limbu-sikkim/', 'Initial local scrape import. Contact enrichment can be added in a later pass.', '["https://gian.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Bishu-limbu.jpeg"]'::jsonb, '["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4oXt60PSbZc","https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l-hdwRdCaec"]'::jsonb, 27.3158027, 88.2753144, 2, 'Bisu Hang Limbu Bisu Hang Lambu, a 22-year-old innovator from West Sikkim, came up with a Selroti maker. Selroti is a traditional sweet bread of Nepali culture. GIAN and the Honey Bee Network accepted and appreciated the innovation. West Sikkim device food machine Selroti Maker Traditionally Selroti is made by hand, but there is a high risk of burning the skin with this flash of hot cooking oil while preparing it. Bisu innovated equipment to use whereby Selroti can be made safely. The device consists of two main components: a food-grade stainless steel cup with a hole for consistent and even flow of batter and a wooden handle attached to it to prevent heat flow to the user’s hand. The Selroti maker is portable, budget-friendly, easy to use, and quickly cleaned. It is helpful to reduce first and second-degree burns on the hands and body of the Selroti maker, increase efficiency and decrease cooking time. It is widely accepted in households in hilly regions. The innovator has sold several units of Selroti makers in Sikkim and West Bengal. It also has high demand in Nepal and Bhutan. Vehicle disinfectant bay by Bisu Hang Limbu (Sikkim) A 22-year-old innovator, Bisu Hang Limbu from West Sikkim, developed an electric disinfecting device designated to sanitize vehicles at checkposts to regulate the spread of coronavirus. GIAN and the Honey Bee Network appreciated and supported this innovation to ensure it can reach the maximum places in and around Sikkim. He is a young inspired innovator who has innovated much other equipment besides vehicle disinfectants, such as the Noha Seleoti maker, Sena 05 Broom, Corn Roaster, Security foot mat, Milk carrying tank, and Crocodile fork, Handset fork. His vehicle disinfectant bay was a useful innovation during COVID-19 and helped the state government maintain the score of zero coronavirus cases.', '{"innovator_name":"Bisu Hang Limbu","location":"West Sikkim","detail_url":"https://gian.org/multilingual_data/selroti-maker/"}'::jsonb, now(), now());


